title: Grateful Dead Live at Ventura County Fairgrounds on 1985-07-14
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi DR-1) -> Sound Devices 744T (24bit/96k) -> Adobe Audition v3.0 -> Samplitude Professional v11.03 -> FLAC/16
description:
Set 1

Hell In A Bucket, They Love Each Other, My Brother Esau, Althea, Cassidy, Big Railroad Blues-> Looks Like Rain-> Might As Well

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Samson & Delilah-> Ship of Fools, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Truckin'-> Smokestack Lightning-> Black Peter-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E: Day Job

reviews.review_text: 4.5 stars A great recording of a great show! For a good AUD, see the Adam/McCue/Ford copy.

So what. They tease with So What before China Cat. I have listened to this show half dozen times never heard that before. I sure do not remember it live, would of been cool though.
 This recording crew is best on archive to my ears. So many rave about Charlie Miller to me though it is the team that puts these together
